 forces and have himself crowned, and she led the French army that raised the siege of Orleans in  1429 . The following year she was captured by the Burgundians and sold to the English, and a year later she was burned at the stake for witchcraft at the age of 18 or 19. Her story has captured the imagination of many writers, and she is variously portrayed as a national and political hero, a model of apolitical straightforwardness and honesty, and a religious heroine. She was canonized in  1920 . More recent influences have included the American film actress  Joan Crawford  (  1908–77 , born  Lucille le Sueur ), the British actress  Joan Collins  (  b. 1933 ), the American comedienne  Joan Rivers  (  b. 1933 ), and the West Indian pop singer  Joan Armatrading  (  b. 1950 )."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705190,"age":20,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705191,"age":45,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705192,"age":58,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705193,"age":67,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705195,"age":112,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Sir John More was born in 1270, in London, England as the son of William More. He married Anges Graunger in 1310, in London, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"1270–":"1270–Surnud","1270–Male":"1270–Surnud","1270–Female":"1270–Surnud","1310–Male":"1310–Surnud","1245–Male":"1245–Surnud","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1245":"1245","1310":"1310","1453":"1453","about 1310":"umbes 1310","1382":"1382","1270":"1270","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","1290":"1290","England":"England","London, England":"London, England"},"fi":{"1270–":"1270–Kuollut","1270–Male":"1270–Kuollut","1270–Female":"1270–Kuollut","1310–Male":"1310–Kuollut","1245–Male":"1245–Kuollut","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1245":"1245","1310":"1310","1453":"1453","about 1310":"noin 1310","1382":"1382","1270":"1270","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","1290":"1290","England":"England","London, England":"London, England"},"fr":{"1270–":"1270–Décédé","1270–Male":"1270–Décédé","1270–Female":"1270–Décédée","1310–Male":"1310–Décédé","1245–Male":"1245–Décédé","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1245":"1245","1310":"1310","1453":"1453","about 1310":"environ 1310","1382":"1382","1270":"1270","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","1290":"1290","England":"Angleterre","London, England":"Londres, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Sir John More est né en 1270, à Londres, Angleterre, fils de William More. Il a épousé Anges Graunger en 1310, à Londres, Angleterre. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"1270–":"1270–Verstorben","1270